x4freetext: REST OF DATA (1.0 TO 30 EV) ON TAPE
AND LOST DATA POINTS (11.413 TO 11.291EV, DPTS =7).
-MEASUREMENT AND NORMALIZATION OF THE RELATIVE U-233
FISSION CROSS-SECTION IN THE LOW RESONANCE REGION.-
MERCURY-COOLED URANIUM TARGET WITH THE ELECTRON
BEAM, WERE SLOWED DOWN BY TWO 4 CM THICK
AND UNDER THE TARGET.   SEVERAL LEAD RINGS
(50 MM THICK) WERE USED TO REDUCE THE GAMMA FLASH.
.U-233 LAYER IN BACK-TO-BACK WITH A LAYER OF B-10.
THE B-10 DEPOSIT IS AN ELEMENTAL BORON LAYER
PREPARED BY EVAPORATION IN VACUUM. ITS THICKNESS
92 PERC B-10, AND ITS DIAM 80 MM. THE U-233 LAYER
WAS PREPARED BY ELECTROSPRAYING OF URANYL ACETATE ON
A 0.3 MM THICK ALUMINIUM DISK. THE THICKNESS OF THE
LAYER IS 1.09 MG/CM**2 OVER A DIAM OF 60 MM, THE
ISOTOPIC COMPOSITION OF THE SAMPLE IS
TIME OF FLIGHT, FLIGHT PATH = 8.1 M (0.008
TO 33 EV, USEFUL REGION 0.02 TO 10 EV) AND 8.3 M
(0.15 TO 50 EV, USEFUL REGION 0.5 TO 30 EV).
IN THE 8.1 M FLIGHT PATH EXPERIMENT THE LINAC
POWER 1.75 KW. THE FILTERS WERE MO (COMMON, ALSO RUN
WITH CD), AND RH, TA, W (BACKGROUND). IN THE 8.3 M
FLIGHT PATH EXPERIMENT THEY WERE   33 NSEC, 400 HZ,
THE U233-FOIL AND THE BORON FOIL (FLUX MONITOR),
WERE MOUNTED BACK-TO-BACK IN THE NEUTRON BEAM
THE BACK-TO-BACK FOILS ARE VIEWED ON
EACH SIDE BY A PAIR OF LARGE SI(AU) SURFACE
RELATIVE TO THE B-10(N,A) CROSS SECTION, AND
AFTERWARDS NORMALIZED TO THE 2200 M/SEC VALUE.
IN THE SECOND RUN THIS NORMALIZATION WAS DONE
IN TWO STEPS USING THE FISSION INTEGRAL
.NO DETAILS GIVEN. ERROR NOT GIVEN IN THE ENERGY
